.row-fluid
  .span5{style: "height: 450px;"}
    %br
    %br
    .main-tag A clean, no bullshit, lightning fast Google Reader alternative
    %br
    %h3.thin 
      Import and save all your Google Reader 
      %br
      subscriptions in one simple click!   
    %br
    %br
    %br
    = link_to image_tag("g2.png"), "/auth/google_oauth2"
    %br
    %br
  .span1{style: "height: 450px;"}
    %br
  .span6{style: "height: 450px;"}
    %h3.red
      = number_to_human(Ref::Entry.count)
      = "articles delivered since launch (#{(Time.now.to_date - Date.new(2013, 6, 3)).to_i.to_s} days ago)"
    = image_tag "reader.png"
.row-fluid
  .span4
    .well
      %h3 Back-up
      Google Reader will shut down on 
      %span.red July 1, 2013. 
      Before that, back-up your subscriptions and folders on pykih reader.
  .span4
    .well
      %h3{style: "padding-bottom: 10px;"} Flag important articles
      = image_tag "stars.png"      
  .span4
    .well
      %h3 Read Later
      Come across an article and want to read it later? Simply click on the spectacles icon and later retrive the articles from the TO READ Folder.
.row-fluid
  .span4
    .well
      %h3 Social Share
      = image_tag "sharing.png"
      Share articles from within the reader.
  .span4
    .well
      %table
        %tr
          %td.span4.top
            = image_tag "github.png"
            %br
            = link_to "Github URL.", "https://github.com/pykih/reader", target: "_blank"
          %td.span8
            %h3 Open source
            Want more features? Develop it. Want a custom deployment? Feel free to deploy it.
  .span4
    %br